# 🏋️ Fitness Tracker App

## 📌 Project Overview

The **Fitness Tracker App** is a Machine Learning-based web application that predicts the number of **calories burned** during physical exercise based on user-specific parameters. The application provides an interactive interface where users can enter their fitness details and instantly receive calorie burn predictions.

The project combines **data analysis**, **machine learning**, and **web application development** using **Python** and **Streamlit**, making it a practical demonstration of predictive analytics in the health and fitness domain.

---

## 🚀 Features

* 🏃 Predicts calories burned during exercise
* 📊 User-friendly interactive web interface
* 👤 Accepts user fitness parameters
* ⚡ Real-time calorie prediction
* 📈 Data preprocessing and feature engineering
* 🤖 Machine Learning-based prediction model
* 💻 Built using Streamlit for easy deployment
* 🎯 Fast and accurate prediction results

---

## 📂 Dataset

The project uses two datasets:

### **exercise.csv**

Contains exercise-related information.

| Feature    | Description                 |
| ---------- | --------------------------- |
| User_ID    | Unique user identifier      |
| Gender     | Male/Female                 |
| Age        | Age of the user             |
| Height     | Height (cm)                 |
| Weight     | Weight (kg)                 |
| Duration   | Exercise duration (minutes) |
| Heart_Rate | Heart rate during exercise  |
| Body_Temp  | Body temperature (°C)       |

### **calories.csv**

Contains the target variable:

| Feature  | Description                     |
| -------- | ------------------------------- |
| Calories | Calories burned during exercise |

The datasets are merged using the **User_ID** column before training the machine learning model.

---

